1
00:00:01,084 --> 00:00:03,420
The Master is Prime Minister
of Great Britain.

2
00:00:03,545 --> 00:00:05,631
And these are my friends.

3
00:00:05,756 --> 00:00:08,008
-They're called the Toclafane.
-What?

4
00:00:08,091 --> 00:00:10,177
-Are you going to tell us who he is?
-He's a Time Lord.

5
00:00:10,260 --> 00:00:13,180
He's cannibalised the Tardis.
It's a paradox machine.

6
00:00:13,263 --> 00:00:16,016
We meet at last, Doctor.

7
00:00:16,099 --> 00:00:18,101
Stop this! Stop it now!

8
00:00:18,727 --> 00:00:20,437
We can't stop him.

9
00:00:20,604 --> 00:00:25,234
Down you go, kids.
Remove one tenth of the population.

10
00:00:25,317 --> 00:00:26,568
I'm coming back.

11
00:00:26,693 --> 00:00:29,363
And the Earth was no more.

12
00:00:29,780 --> 00:00:31,949
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

13
00:01:09,069 --> 00:01:13,115
WOMAN: Spacelane traffic is advised
to stay away from SOL 3,

14
00:01:13,198 --> 00:01:14,908
also known as Earth.

15
00:01:14,992 --> 00:01:19,329
Pilots are warned SOL 3
ls now entering terminal extinction.

16
00:01:19,538 --> 00:01:21,498
Planet Earth is closed.

17
00:01:21,748 --> 00:01:26,420
Planet Earth is closed.
Planet Earth is closed.

18
00:02:00,329 --> 00:02:02,289
-What's your name, then?
-Tom Milligan.

19
00:02:02,372 --> 00:02:05,917
No need to ask who you are,
the famous Martha Jones.

20
00:02:06,001 --> 00:02:07,753
How long since you were last in Britain?

21
00:02:07,836 --> 00:02:11,590
365 days. It's been a long year.

22
00:02:11,965 --> 00:02:13,383
So what's the plan?

23
00:02:13,467 --> 00:02:16,887
This Professor Docherty,
I need to see her. Can you get me there?

24
00:02:16,970 --> 00:02:20,057
She works in a repair shed, Nuclear
Plant Seven. I can get you inside.

25
00:02:20,140 --> 00:02:22,392
What's this all for?
What's so important about her?

26
00:02:22,476 --> 00:02:25,646
Sorry. The more you know,
the more you're at risk.

27
00:02:25,729 --> 00:02:28,565
There's a lot of people depending
on you. You're a bit of a legend.

28
00:02:28,649 --> 00:02:30,400
And what does the legend say?

29
00:02:30,484 --> 00:02:32,986
That you sailed the Atlantic,
walked across America,

30
00:02:33,070 --> 00:02:35,989
that you were the only person
to get out of Japan alive.

31
00:02:36,073 --> 00:02:39,493
Martha Jones, they say,
she's gonna save the world.

32
00:02:39,576 --> 00:02:41,036
A bit late for that.

33
00:02:41,119 --> 00:02:43,664
How come you can drive?
Don't you get stopped?

34
00:02:43,747 --> 00:02:47,626
Medical staff. Used to be
in paediatrics back in the old days.

35
00:02:47,709 --> 00:02:50,921
But that gives me a licence to travel
so I can help out at the lab our camps.

36
00:02:51,004 --> 00:02:53,590
Great. I'm travelling with a doctor.

37
00:02:57,594 --> 00:03:01,098
Story goes that you're the only person
on Earth who can kill him.

38
00:03:01,181 --> 00:03:05,018
That you and you alone
can kill the Master stone dead.

39
00:03:05,102 --> 00:03:07,187
Let's just drive.

40
00:03:15,445 --> 00:03:17,489
ON PA: Citizens, rejoice!

41
00:03:17,572 --> 00:03:20,575
Your Lord and Master stands on high!

42
00:03:20,659 --> 00:03:22,869
Playing track three.

43
00:03:22,953 --> 00:03:24,788
# I can't decide

44
00:03:24,871 --> 00:03:27,374
# Whether you should live or die

45
00:03:27,457 --> 00:03:29,876
# Oh, you'll probably go to heaven

46
00:03:29,960 --> 00:03:32,254
# Please don't hang your head and cry

47
00:03:32,337 --> 00:03:33,463
# No wonder why

48
00:03:33,588 --> 00:03:35,632
# My heart feels dead inside

49
00:03:35,716 --> 00:03:38,343
# It's cold and hard and petrified

50
00:03:38,468 --> 00:03:40,846
# Lock the doors and close the blinds

51
00:03:40,971 --> 00:03:42,931
# We're going for a ride

52
00:03:43,014 --> 00:03:45,100
# Oh, I could throw you in the lake

53
00:03:45,183 --> 00:03:47,644
# Or feed you poisoned birthday cake

54
00:03:47,728 --> 00:03:52,107
# I won't deny
I'm gonna miss you when you're gone

55
00:03:53,024 --> 00:03:55,527
# Oh, I could bury you alive

56
00:03:55,652 --> 00:03:58,196
# But you might crawl out with a knife

57
00:03:58,280 --> 00:04:01,533
# And kill me when I'm sleeping
That's why

58
00:04:01,616 --> 00:04:03,493
# I can't decide

59
00:04:03,618 --> 00:04:06,079
# Whether you should live or die

60
00:04:06,163 --> 00:04:08,540
# Oh, you'll probably go to heaven

61
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:10,917
# Please don't hang your head and cry

62
00:04:11,001 --> 00:04:12,586
# I wonder why

63
00:04:12,669 --> 00:04:14,337
# My heart feels dead inside

64
00:04:14,463 --> 00:04:17,090
# It's cold and hard and petrified

65
00:04:17,174 --> 00:04:19,760
# Lock the doors
and close the blinds... #

66
00:04:19,843 --> 00:04:22,053
It's ready to rise, Doctor.

67
00:04:22,554 --> 00:04:26,892
The new Time Lord Empire.
It's good, isn't it? Isn't it, good?

68
00:04:26,975 --> 00:04:28,435
Anything?

69
00:04:29,519 --> 00:04:31,146
No? Anything?

70
00:04:34,524 --> 00:04:39,112
Oh, but they broke your heart,
didn't they, those Toclafane?

71
00:04:39,196 --> 00:04:41,948
Ever since you worked out
what they really are.

72
00:04:42,032 --> 00:04:45,410
They say Martha Jones

73
00:04:46,411 --> 00:04:48,205
has come back home.

74
00:04:48,330 --> 00:04:50,874
Now why would she do that?

75
00:04:50,957 --> 00:04:52,209
Leave her alone.

76
00:04:52,334 --> 00:04:54,169
But you said something to her,
didn't you?

77
00:04:55,003 --> 00:04:57,130
On the day I took control.

78
00:04:59,549 --> 00:05:03,303
-What did you tell her?
-I have one thing to say to you.

79
00:05:04,387 --> 00:05:07,307
-You know what it is.
-Oh, no you don't!

80
00:05:08,099 --> 00:05:10,727
Valiant now entering Zone One airspace.

81
00:05:10,811 --> 00:05:14,439
-Citizens, rejoice!
-Come on, people! What are we doing?

82
00:05:15,065 --> 00:05:17,943
Launch day in 24 hours!

83
00:05:36,419 --> 00:05:37,963
Morning, Tish!

84
00:05:38,922 --> 00:05:41,258
Ah! Smell that sea air!

85
00:05:42,008 --> 00:05:44,761
Makes me long
for good old British fish and chips.

86
00:05:44,886 --> 00:05:46,179
(JACK LAUGHING)

87
00:05:46,263 --> 00:05:49,015
And what do I get? Cold mashed swede.

88
00:05:49,307 --> 00:05:52,519
Some hotel.
Last time I book over the internet.

89
00:05:57,941 --> 00:05:59,860
MARTHA: All over the Earth,
those things.

90
00:05:59,943 --> 00:06:02,487
He's even carved himself
into Mount Rushmore.

91
00:06:02,612 --> 00:06:04,406
Best to keep down.

92
00:06:05,782 --> 00:06:07,450
Here we go.

93
00:06:09,411 --> 00:06:13,748
The entire South Coast of England
converted into shipyards.

94
00:06:13,832 --> 00:06:16,126
They bring in slave lab our
every morning,

95
00:06:16,251 --> 00:06:19,212
break up cars, houses, anything,
just for the metal,

96
00:06:19,296 --> 00:06:21,715
building the fleet out of scrap.

97
00:06:21,798 --> 00:06:25,260
You should see Russia.
That's Shipyard Number One.

98
00:06:25,343 --> 00:06:27,387
All the way from the Black Sea
to the Bering Strait,

99
00:06:27,470 --> 00:06:30,140
there's 100,000 rockets
getting ready for war.

100
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:33,143
-War? With who?
-The rest of the universe.

101
00:06:33,476 --> 00:06:36,897
I've been out there, Tom, in space,
before all this happened,

102
00:06:37,022 --> 00:06:39,983
and there's 1,000 different
civilisations all around us

103
00:06:40,066 --> 00:06:41,902
with no idea of what's happening here.

104
00:06:41,985 --> 00:06:44,404
The Master can build weapons
big enough to devastate them all.

105
00:06:44,487 --> 00:06:46,364
-You've been in space?
-Problem with that?

106
00:06:46,489 --> 00:06:49,618
No! No, just... Wow.

107
00:06:50,493 --> 00:06:53,914
-Anything else I should know?
-I've met Shakespeare.

108
00:06:54,664 --> 00:06:56,374
(SPHERES WHIRRING)

109
00:06:59,502 --> 00:07:02,631
-SPHERE: Identify, little man.
-I've got a licence!

110
00:07:02,714 --> 00:07:06,635
Thomas Milligan, Peripatetic Medical
Squad. I'm allowed to travel.

111
00:07:06,718 --> 00:07:10,597
-I was just checking for...
-Soon the rockets will fly!

112
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:14,684
SPHERE 2: And everyone will need
medicine! You'll be so busy!

113
00:07:14,809 --> 00:07:17,020
(SPHERES LAUGHING)

114
00:07:23,193 --> 00:07:26,780
But...they didn't see you.

115
00:07:26,863 --> 00:07:29,699
How do you think I travelled the world?

116
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:33,244
The Master set up Archangel,
that mobile phone network,

117
00:07:33,328 --> 00:07:35,121
15 satellites around the planet.

118
00:07:35,205 --> 00:07:37,374
But really it's transmitting
this low-level psychic field.

119
00:07:37,457 --> 00:07:40,043
That's how everyone got hypnotised
into thinking he was Harold Saxon.

120
00:07:40,168 --> 00:07:42,045
Saxon! Feels like years ago.

121
00:07:42,170 --> 00:07:44,506
But the key's tuned in
to the same frequency.

122
00:07:44,631 --> 00:07:48,677
Makes me sort of, not invisible,
just unnoticeable.

123
00:07:49,219 --> 00:07:52,681
-Well, I can see you.
-That's 'cause you wanted to.

124
00:07:54,224 --> 00:07:56,059
Yeah, I suppose I did.

125
00:07:56,142 --> 00:07:58,561
-Is there a Mrs Milligan?
-No.

126
00:07:58,895 --> 00:08:01,481
-No. What about you?
-There used to be someone.

127
00:08:11,157 --> 00:08:13,034
Long time ago.

128
00:08:14,577 --> 00:08:16,788
Come on, I've got to find
this Docherty woman.

129
00:08:16,913 --> 00:08:18,832
Well, we'll have to wait
till the next work shift.

130
00:08:18,915 --> 00:08:21,584
-What time is it now?
-It's nearly 3:00.

131
00:08:44,232 --> 00:08:46,609
Time for my massage.
Who shall I have today?

132
00:08:46,693 --> 00:08:49,029
Tanya! Come on, sweetheart.

133
00:08:49,112 --> 00:08:51,614
Lucy, have you met Tanya?
She's gorgeous!

134
00:08:51,740 --> 00:08:53,867
Tanya, when we go to the stars,

135
00:08:53,950 --> 00:08:58,663
I'm going to take you to
the Catrigan Nova. Whirlpools of gold.

136
00:09:04,669 --> 00:09:07,797
You two should get to know each other.
That might be fun.

137
00:09:24,606 --> 00:09:28,109
-What the hell?
-Condition red! Repeat, condition red!

138
00:09:34,407 --> 00:09:36,993
-Oh, I see.
-I told you.

139
00:09:37,911 --> 00:09:39,913
I have one thing to say.

140
00:09:50,965 --> 00:09:52,842
Oh, here we go again.

141
00:09:56,346 --> 00:09:58,681
Isomorphic controls.

142
00:10:01,518 --> 00:10:04,270
Which means they only work for me.

143
00:10:05,438 --> 00:10:06,606
Like this!

144
00:10:07,190 --> 00:10:09,150
-Say sorry!
-Sorry, sorry!

145
00:10:09,234 --> 00:10:10,693
-Mum!
-Sorry!

146
00:10:11,778 --> 00:10:15,615
Didn't you learn anything
from the blessed St Martha?

147
00:10:18,535 --> 00:10:23,373
Siding with the Doctor
is a very dangerous thing to do.

148
00:10:23,790 --> 00:10:25,375
Take them away.

149
00:10:25,458 --> 00:10:28,128
MAN: Move! Come on.
MASTER: Okay, got you.

150
00:10:28,586 --> 00:10:30,213
(GRUNTING)

151
00:10:30,296 --> 00:10:32,173
There you go, gramps.

152
00:10:33,633 --> 00:10:35,593
Oh! Do you know...

153
00:10:35,718 --> 00:10:39,139
I remember the days when the Doctor,

154
00:10:39,222 --> 00:10:44,227
oh, that famous Doctor,
was waging a Time War,

155
00:10:44,310 --> 00:10:47,856
battling Sea Devils and Axons.

156
00:10:47,939 --> 00:10:52,318
He sealed the rift
at the Medusa Cascade single-handed!

157
00:10:54,028 --> 00:10:56,239
And look at him now.

158
00:10:56,322 --> 00:10:59,951
Stealing screwdrivers.
How did he ever come to this?

159
00:11:01,369 --> 00:11:02,912
Oh, yeah! Me!

160
00:11:04,205 --> 00:11:08,042
I just need you to listen.

161
00:11:08,126 --> 00:11:11,129
No, it's my turn.

162
00:11:12,046 --> 00:11:15,592
Revenge! Best served hot!

163
00:11:15,717 --> 00:11:19,637
And this time
it's a message for Miss Jones.

164
00:11:31,983 --> 00:11:34,110
(GRUNTING)

165
00:11:34,194 --> 00:11:36,321
-Professor Docherty?
-Busy.

166
00:11:36,946 --> 00:11:40,491
They sent word ahead. I'm Tom Milligan.
This is Martha Jones.

167
00:11:40,575 --> 00:11:43,536
She can be the Queen of Sheba
for all I care, I'm still busy.

168
00:11:43,620 --> 00:11:47,540
-Televisions don't work any more.
-Oh, God, I miss Countdown.

169
00:11:47,624 --> 00:11:51,085
Never been the same since Des took over.
Both Deses.

170
00:11:51,502 --> 00:11:54,631
What's the plural for Des?
Desii? Deseen?

171
00:11:54,756 --> 00:11:58,176
But we've been told
there's gonna be a transmission.

172
00:11:59,135 --> 00:12:01,763
From the man himself! There!

173
00:12:03,139 --> 00:12:05,642
My people! Salutations.

174
00:12:06,392 --> 00:12:10,063
On this, the eve of war. Lovely woman.

175
00:12:10,146 --> 00:12:13,524
But I know there's
all sorts of whispers down there,

176
00:12:13,650 --> 00:12:18,154
stories of a child walking the Earth,
giving you hope.

177
00:12:20,865 --> 00:12:25,161
But I ask you,
how much hope has this man got?

178
00:12:26,537 --> 00:12:28,331
Say hello, Gandalf!

179
00:12:29,374 --> 00:12:33,544
Except he's not that old,
but he's an alien

180
00:12:33,628 --> 00:12:38,591
with a much greater lifespan
than you stunted little apes.

181
00:12:39,008 --> 00:12:40,843
What if it showed?

182
00:12:40,927 --> 00:12:44,013
What if I suspend
your capacity to regenerate?

183
00:12:47,267 --> 00:12:51,938
All 900 years of your life, Doctor,
what if we could see them?

184
00:12:56,442 --> 00:13:02,532
Older and older and older.

185
00:13:04,993 --> 00:13:07,036
Down you go, Doctor!

186
00:13:08,496 --> 00:13:10,957
Down, down.

187
00:13:12,041 --> 00:13:14,335
Down the years.

188
00:13:29,851 --> 00:13:31,102
Doctor?

189
00:14:04,427 --> 00:14:08,222
Received and understood, Miss Jones?

190
00:14:12,268 --> 00:14:13,603
I'm sorry.

191
00:14:16,522 --> 00:14:18,608
The Doctor's still alive.

192
00:14:21,778 --> 00:14:23,571
Obviously, the Archangel network

193
00:14:23,654 --> 00:14:26,949
would seem to be
the Master's greatest weakness.

194
00:14:27,992 --> 00:14:32,038
15 satellites all around the Earth
still transmitting.

195
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:34,123
That's why there's so little resistance.

196
00:14:34,207 --> 00:14:38,336
It's broadcasting a telepathic signal
that keeps people scared.

197
00:14:39,170 --> 00:14:40,922
We could just take them out.

198
00:14:41,005 --> 00:14:44,592
We could. 15 ground-to-air missiles.
You got any on you?

199
00:14:44,675 --> 00:14:47,387
Besides, any military action,
the Toclafane descend.

200
00:14:47,470 --> 00:14:50,098
They're not called Toclafane.
That's a name the Master made up.

201
00:14:50,181 --> 00:14:51,265
What are they, then?

202
00:14:51,349 --> 00:14:54,894
Well, that's why I came to find you.
Know your enemy.

203
00:14:55,895 --> 00:14:57,438
I've got this.

204
00:14:58,231 --> 00:15:01,818
No one's been able to look at a sphere
close up. They can't even be damaged.

205
00:15:01,901 --> 00:15:05,738
Except once. A lightning strike in
South Africa brought one of them down.

206
00:15:05,822 --> 00:15:08,991
Just by chance.
I've got the readings on this.

207
00:15:09,575 --> 00:15:10,660
Oh!

208
00:15:12,662 --> 00:15:14,705
Whoever thought we'd miss Bill Gates?

209
00:15:14,831 --> 00:15:17,333
So is that why you travelled the world?
To find a disc?

210
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:19,043
No, just got lucky.

211
00:15:19,168 --> 00:15:21,170
I heard stories
that you walked the Earth

212
00:15:21,295 --> 00:15:23,714
to find a way to build a weapon.

213
00:15:27,218 --> 00:15:28,678
There!

214
00:15:28,761 --> 00:15:31,389
"A current of 58.5 kiloamperes

215
00:15:31,472 --> 00:15:35,685
"transfer a charge
of 510 megajoules precisely.”

216
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:39,772
-Can you recreate that?
-I think so. Easily, yes.

217
00:15:40,022 --> 00:15:44,026
Right then, Dr Milligan.
We're gonna get us a sphere.

218
00:16:12,555 --> 00:16:16,225
-He's coming! You ready?
-You do your job, I'll do mine!

219
00:16:18,436 --> 00:16:19,562
Now!

220
00:16:28,529 --> 00:16:30,156
(BUZZING)

221
00:16:33,034 --> 00:16:35,119
That's only half the job.

222
00:16:36,245 --> 00:16:39,207
Let's find out what's inside.

223
00:16:50,593 --> 00:16:54,931
FRANCINE: I'm going kill him
if I have to wait 100 years.

224
00:16:55,348 --> 00:16:57,600
I'm going to kill the Master.

225
00:16:57,975 --> 00:17:02,688
One day, he'll let his guard down.
One day. And I'll be there.

226
00:17:02,939 --> 00:17:04,982
No, that's my job.

227
00:17:07,026 --> 00:17:11,197
I swear to you,
I'd shoot that man stone dead.

228
00:17:16,369 --> 00:17:20,164
I'll get him, even if it kills me.

229
00:17:20,289 --> 00:17:22,542
-Don't say that.
-I mean it.

230
00:17:22,625 --> 00:17:26,754
That man made us stand on deck
and watch the islands of Japan burning.

231
00:17:26,837 --> 00:17:28,631
Millions of people.

232
00:17:29,465 --> 00:17:32,343
I swear to you, he's dead.

233
00:17:36,389 --> 00:17:38,266
Tomorrow they launch.

234
00:17:41,644 --> 00:17:45,314
We're opening up a rift
in the Braccatolian space.

235
00:17:47,024 --> 00:17:51,195
-Won't see us coming. Kind of scary.
-Then stop.

236
00:17:51,487 --> 00:17:53,823
Once the empire is established

237
00:17:53,948 --> 00:17:58,995
and there's a new Gallifrey
in the heavens, maybe then it stops.

238
00:18:05,835 --> 00:18:07,336
The drumming.

239
00:18:09,255 --> 00:18:11,215
The never-ending drumbeat.

240
00:18:12,383 --> 00:18:15,344
Ever since I was a child,
I looked into the Vortex.

241
00:18:15,428 --> 00:18:19,557
That's when it chose me.
The drumming, the call to war.

242
00:18:20,141 --> 00:18:21,851
Can't you hear it?

243
00:18:24,145 --> 00:18:28,524
Listen, it's there now, right now.
Tell me you can hear it, Doctor.

244
00:18:30,860 --> 00:18:33,029
-Tell me.
-It's only you.

245
00:18:34,280 --> 00:18:35,489
Good.

246
00:18:37,617 --> 00:18:42,997
SPHERE: Tomorrow, the war!
Tomorrow we rise, never to fall!

247
00:18:43,289 --> 00:18:47,710
You see? I'm doing it for them.
You should be grateful.

248
00:18:47,793 --> 00:18:49,837
After all, you love them.

249
00:18:50,838 --> 00:18:52,715
So very, very much.

250
00:18:54,592 --> 00:18:59,972
There's some sort of magnetic clamp.
Hold on, I'll just trip the...

251
00:19:14,070 --> 00:19:15,696
Oh, my God!

252
00:19:26,457 --> 00:19:27,917
It's alive!

253
00:19:29,043 --> 00:19:31,462
Martha. Martha Jones.

254
00:19:32,213 --> 00:19:33,381
It knows you.

255
00:19:33,464 --> 00:19:36,592
Sweet, kind Martha Jones.
You helped us to fly.

256
00:19:36,717 --> 00:19:39,178
-What do you mean?
-You led us to salvation.

257
00:19:39,261 --> 00:19:42,348
-Who are you?
-The skies are made of diamonds.

258
00:19:42,431 --> 00:19:43,724
No.

259
00:19:44,767 --> 00:19:45,935
You can't be him.

260
00:19:46,352 --> 00:19:48,521
The skies are made of diamonds.

261
00:19:51,273 --> 00:19:54,652
We share each other's memories.
You sent him to Utopia.

262
00:19:54,777 --> 00:19:55,945
Oh, my God!

263
00:19:56,028 --> 00:19:57,780
What's it talking about? What's it mean?

264
00:19:57,905 --> 00:20:02,284
-What are they?
-Martha. Martha, tell us. What are they?

265
00:20:04,370 --> 00:20:06,914
They're us. They're humans.

266
00:20:07,623 --> 00:20:09,959
The human race from the future.

267
00:20:11,752 --> 00:20:13,504
I took Lucy to Utopia.

268
00:20:15,464 --> 00:20:18,134
A Time Lord and his human companion.

269
00:20:19,635 --> 00:20:23,472
I took her to see the stars.
Isn't that right, sweetheart?

270
00:20:23,597 --> 00:20:28,394
Trillions of years into the future.
To the end of the universe.

271
00:20:28,811 --> 00:20:32,148
-Tell him what you saw.
-Dying. Everything dying.

272
00:20:32,982 --> 00:20:37,319
The whole of creation was falling apart.
And I thought, "There's no point.

273
00:20:37,403 --> 00:20:41,323
-"No point to anything. Not ever."
-And it's all your fault.

274
00:20:42,283 --> 00:20:44,744
I'd sort of worked it out,
with the paradox machine,

275
00:20:44,827 --> 00:20:46,328
because the Doctor said,

276
00:20:46,412 --> 00:20:48,789
on the day before
the Master came to power, he said...

277
00:20:49,165 --> 00:20:50,458
When he was stealing the Tardis,

278
00:20:50,541 --> 00:20:54,003
the only thing I could do
was fuse the coordinates.

279
00:20:56,255 --> 00:20:58,215
I locked them permanently.

280
00:20:58,340 --> 00:21:00,384
He could only travel
between the year 100 trillion

281
00:21:00,509 --> 00:21:03,429
and the last place the Tardis landed.
Which is right here, right now.

282
00:21:03,679 --> 00:21:07,183
The Master had the Tardis,
this time machine.

283
00:21:07,349 --> 00:21:10,478
But the only other place he could go
was the end of the universe,

284
00:21:10,561 --> 00:21:11,854
so he found Utopia.

285
00:21:11,979 --> 00:21:16,025
You should have seen it, Doctor.
Furnaces. Burning.

286
00:21:17,693 --> 00:21:20,654
The last of humanity
screaming at the dark.

287
00:21:20,905 --> 00:21:23,616
The Utopia project was the last hope.

288
00:21:24,784 --> 00:21:28,037
Trying to find a way
to escape the end of everything.

289
00:21:28,120 --> 00:21:32,833
There was no solution. No diamonds.
Just the dark and the cold.

290
00:21:32,958 --> 00:21:37,296
All that human invention that had
sustained them across the aeons,

291
00:21:37,379 --> 00:21:40,633
it all turned inward.
They cannibalised themselves.

292
00:21:40,716 --> 00:21:42,301
SPHERE: We made ourselves so pretty.

293
00:21:42,384 --> 00:21:45,012
Regressing into children,
but it didn't work.

294
00:21:45,095 --> 00:21:47,264
MASTER: The universe
was collapsing around them.

295
00:21:47,389 --> 00:21:50,434
But then the Master came
with his wonderful time machine,

296
00:21:50,559 --> 00:21:52,645
to bring us back home.

297
00:21:52,728 --> 00:21:55,606
But that's a paradox.
If you're the future of the human race,

298
00:21:55,689 --> 00:21:57,608
and you've come back
to murder your ancestors,

299
00:21:57,733 --> 00:22:01,278
you should cancel yourselves out.
You shouldn't exist.

300
00:22:01,695 --> 00:22:03,197
And that's the paradox machine.

301
00:22:03,280 --> 00:22:05,407
(LAUGHING)

302
00:22:07,409 --> 00:22:09,537
My masterpiece, Doctor.

303
00:22:09,620 --> 00:22:13,415
A living Tardis, strong enough
to hold the paradox in place.

304
00:22:13,499 --> 00:22:18,671
Allowing the past and the future
to collide in infinite majesty.

305
00:22:19,588 --> 00:22:21,799
But you're changing history.

306
00:22:23,759 --> 00:22:26,887
Not just Earth, the entire universe.

307
00:22:26,971 --> 00:22:30,683
I'm a Time Lord. I have that right.

308
00:22:31,559 --> 00:22:33,102
But even then...

309
00:22:34,311 --> 00:22:37,565
why come all this way just to destroy?

310
00:22:37,982 --> 00:22:41,777
We come backwards in time
all to build a brand-new empire

311
00:22:41,861 --> 00:22:44,446
lasting 100 trillion years!

312
00:22:44,947 --> 00:22:46,949
With me as their Master.

313
00:22:48,909 --> 00:22:50,828
Time Lord and humans combined.

314
00:22:50,911 --> 00:22:53,747
Haven't you always
dreamt of that, Doctor?

315
00:22:53,831 --> 00:22:56,458
What about us? We're the same species.

316
00:22:56,542 --> 00:22:59,169
-Why do you kill so many of us?
-Because it's fun.

317
00:22:59,253 --> 00:23:01,130
(LAUGHING)

318
00:23:06,802 --> 00:23:10,598
Human race.
Greatest monsters of them all.

319
00:23:16,645 --> 00:23:18,564
Night, then.

320
00:23:32,953 --> 00:23:36,123
I think it's time
we had the truth, Miss Jones.

321
00:23:37,249 --> 00:23:41,545
Legend says you travelled the world
to find a way of killing the Master.

322
00:23:41,670 --> 00:23:43,547
Tell us, is it true?

323
00:23:46,216 --> 00:23:48,844
Just before I escaped,
the Doctor told me...

324
00:23:54,058 --> 00:23:57,353
The Doctor and the Master,
they've been coming to Earth for years.

325
00:23:57,436 --> 00:23:59,104
And they've been watched.

326
00:23:59,188 --> 00:24:03,192
There's UNIT and Torchwood,
all studying Time Lords in secret.

327
00:24:03,692 --> 00:24:06,445
And they made this,
the ultimate defence.

328
00:24:06,528 --> 00:24:09,198
All you need is to get close,
I can shoot the Master dead with this.

329
00:24:09,281 --> 00:24:11,951
Actually, you can put that down now,
thank you very much.

330
00:24:12,034 --> 00:24:14,203
Point is, it's not so easy
to kill a Time Lord.

331
00:24:14,286 --> 00:24:17,790
They can regenerate,
literally bring themselves back to life.

332
00:24:17,873 --> 00:24:21,627
-Ah, the Master's immortal! Wonderful!
-Except for this.

333
00:24:23,504 --> 00:24:25,506
Four chemicals slotted into the gun.

334
00:24:25,589 --> 00:24:29,885
Inject him,
kills a Time Lord permanently.

335
00:24:29,969 --> 00:24:33,681
-Four chemicals, you've only got three.
-Still need the last one.

336
00:24:33,764 --> 00:24:35,724
'Cause the components of this gun
were kept safe,

337
00:24:35,849 --> 00:24:38,227
scattered across the world,
and I found them.

338
00:24:38,352 --> 00:24:40,688
San Diego, Beijing, Budapest and London.

339
00:24:40,771 --> 00:24:41,855
Then where is it?

340
00:24:41,939 --> 00:24:43,774
There's an old UNIT base
in North London.

341
00:24:43,857 --> 00:24:47,069
I've found the access codes.
Tom, you've got to get me there.

342
00:24:47,152 --> 00:24:48,487
We can't get across London in the dark.

343
00:24:48,612 --> 00:24:51,031
It's full of wild dogs,
we'll get eaten alive.

344
00:24:51,115 --> 00:24:53,826
We can wait till the morning
then go with the medical convoy.

345
00:24:53,909 --> 00:24:55,744
You can spend the night here,
if you like.

346
00:24:55,828 --> 00:24:59,081
No, we can get halfway,
stay at the slave quarters in Bexley.

347
00:24:59,164 --> 00:25:02,292
-Professor, thank you.
-Oh, and you. Good luck.

348
00:25:03,419 --> 00:25:04,628
Thanks.

349
00:25:09,633 --> 00:25:12,553
Martha. Could you do it?

350
00:25:13,679 --> 00:25:17,182
-Could you actually kill him?
-Got no choice.

351
00:25:17,266 --> 00:25:21,437
You might be many things,
but you don't look like a killer to me.

352
00:25:43,459 --> 00:25:45,586
Let me in, it's Milligan.

353
00:25:47,629 --> 00:25:50,340
-Did you bring food?
-Couldn't get any. And I'm starving.

354
00:25:50,424 --> 00:25:52,217
WOMAN: All we've got is water.

355
00:25:52,301 --> 00:25:55,554
-MARTHA: Sorry.
-It's cheaper than building barracks.

356
00:25:55,637 --> 00:25:57,639
Pack them in, 100 in each house,

357
00:25:57,723 --> 00:25:59,850
ferry them off
to the shipyards every morning.

358
00:25:59,975 --> 00:26:02,227
-Are you Martha Jones?
-Yeah, that's me.

359
00:26:02,311 --> 00:26:05,397
Can you kill him? They said
you can kill the Master. Can you?

360
00:26:05,481 --> 00:26:08,067
Tell us you can do it.
Please, tell us you can do it.

361
00:26:08,150 --> 00:26:09,818
WOMAN: Who is the Master?

362
00:26:09,902 --> 00:26:12,279
(ALL CHATTERING)

363
00:26:12,362 --> 00:26:14,615
Come on, just leave her alone.
She's exhausted.

364
00:26:14,698 --> 00:26:16,575
No, it's all right.

365
00:26:16,658 --> 00:26:18,827
They want me to talk and I will.

366
00:26:25,667 --> 00:26:29,505
Access Priority One.
This is Professor Alison Docherty.

367
00:26:29,630 --> 00:26:31,590
State your intent.

368
00:26:31,673 --> 00:26:34,134
First of all,
I need to know about my son.

369
00:26:34,218 --> 00:26:35,886
State your intent.

370
00:26:35,969 --> 00:26:38,680
Is my son still alive?

371
00:26:38,931 --> 00:26:40,682
State your intent.

372
00:26:44,853 --> 00:26:47,689
I have some information for the Master.

373
00:26:50,776 --> 00:26:52,778
Concerning Martha Jones.

374
00:27:02,538 --> 00:27:03,831
Guess what?

375
00:27:04,206 --> 00:27:06,500
I travelled across the world.

376
00:27:06,583 --> 00:27:09,294
From the ruins of New York
to the Fusion Mills of China,

377
00:27:09,378 --> 00:27:12,256
right across
the Radiation Pits of Europe.

378
00:27:12,381 --> 00:27:16,593
And everywhere I went I saw people
just like you, living as slaves.

379
00:27:16,677 --> 00:27:19,471
But if Martha Jones became a legend,
then that's wrong,

380
00:27:19,555 --> 00:27:23,142
because my name isn't important.
There's someone else.

381
00:27:24,101 --> 00:27:28,647
The man who sent me out there.
The man who told me to walk the Earth.

382
00:27:28,730 --> 00:27:31,733
And his name is the Doctor.

383
00:27:32,568 --> 00:27:37,072
He has saved your lives so many times
and you never even knew he was there.

384
00:27:37,197 --> 00:27:40,075
He never stops, he never stays,

385
00:27:40,868 --> 00:27:43,162
he never asks to be thanked.

386
00:27:43,245 --> 00:27:46,582
But I've seen him. I know him.

387
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:49,751
I love him.

388
00:27:53,297 --> 00:27:55,382
And I know what he can do.

389
00:27:55,465 --> 00:27:59,511
It's him! It's him! My God, it's him!
It's the Master! He's here!

390
00:27:59,595 --> 00:28:02,514
But he never comes to Earth!
He never walks upon the ground.

391
00:28:02,598 --> 00:28:03,932
Hide her!

392
00:28:17,821 --> 00:28:20,824
He walks among us, our Lord and Master.

393
00:28:21,033 --> 00:28:26,580
Martha! Martha Jones! I can see you.

394
00:28:26,872 --> 00:28:30,459
Out you come, little girl.
Come and meet your Master.

395
00:28:36,882 --> 00:28:39,468
Anybody? Nobody? No? Nothing?

396
00:28:40,260 --> 00:28:41,428
Positions!

397
00:28:41,553 --> 00:28:42,638
(GUNS COCKING)

398
00:28:45,682 --> 00:28:48,810
I'll give the order
unless you surrender.

399
00:28:48,936 --> 00:28:52,814
Ask yourself,
"What would the Doctor do?"

400
00:29:22,803 --> 00:29:27,516
Oh, yes! Oh, very well done! Good girl!

401
00:29:28,058 --> 00:29:29,851
He trained you well.

402
00:29:32,312 --> 00:29:34,231
Bag. Give me the bag.

403
00:29:36,233 --> 00:29:38,777
No, stay there, just throw it.

404
00:29:50,706 --> 00:29:53,709
And now, good companion,
your work is done.

405
00:29:54,501 --> 00:29:55,585
No!

406
00:30:05,554 --> 00:30:10,434
But you, when you die,
the Doctor should be witness, hmm?

407
00:30:13,395 --> 00:30:14,896
(INHALING)

408
00:30:15,814 --> 00:30:17,691
Almost dawn, Martha,

409
00:30:19,484 --> 00:30:23,030
and planet Earth marches to war.

410
00:30:23,905 --> 00:30:27,200
ON PA: Citizens of Earth,
rejoice and observe.

411
00:30:52,934 --> 00:30:56,646
Your teleport device,
in case you thought I'd forgotten.

412
00:31:04,112 --> 00:31:05,781
And now

413
00:31:06,448 --> 00:31:07,991
kneel.

414
00:31:09,493 --> 00:31:12,287
Down below,
the fleet is ready to launch.

415
00:31:12,412 --> 00:31:18,001
200,000 ships set
to burn across the universe.

416
00:31:21,922 --> 00:31:23,423
Are we ready?

417
00:31:23,507 --> 00:31:26,468
MAN: The fleet awaits your signal,
rejoice!

418
00:31:27,469 --> 00:31:30,305
Three minutes
to align the Black Hole Convertors.

419
00:31:31,640 --> 00:31:33,183
Counting down!

420
00:31:35,143 --> 00:31:37,854
I never could resist a ticking clock.

421
00:31:37,979 --> 00:31:40,232
My children, are you ready?

422
00:31:40,315 --> 00:31:45,737
ALL: We will fly and blaze and slice!
We will fly and blaze and slice!

423
00:31:45,904 --> 00:31:48,532
At zero, to mark this day,

424
00:31:49,282 --> 00:31:52,244
the child, Martha Jones, will die.

425
00:31:52,994 --> 00:31:54,538
My first blood.

426
00:31:55,163 --> 00:31:57,666
Any last words? No?

427
00:32:01,628 --> 00:32:05,132
Such a disappointment, this one.
Days of old, Doctor,

428
00:32:05,257 --> 00:32:08,802
you had companions
who could absorb the Time Vortex!

429
00:32:08,885 --> 00:32:11,847
This one's useless! Bow your head.

430
00:32:13,014 --> 00:32:16,143
And so it falls to me, as Master of all,

431
00:32:16,226 --> 00:32:20,522
to establish from this day
a new order of Time Lords.

432
00:32:20,605 --> 00:32:22,232
From this day forward...

433
00:32:22,357 --> 00:32:24,025
(LAUGHING SOFTLY)

434
00:32:24,693 --> 00:32:27,362
What? What's so funny?

435
00:32:29,489 --> 00:32:31,283
-A gun?
-What about it?

436
00:32:31,366 --> 00:32:34,661
-A gun in four parts?
-Yes, and I destroyed it.

437
00:32:34,744 --> 00:32:37,038
A gun, in four parts,
scattered across the world?

438
00:32:37,164 --> 00:32:40,959
I mean, come on!
Did you really believe that?

439
00:32:41,042 --> 00:32:44,379
-What do you mean?
-As if I would ask her to kill.

440
00:32:44,713 --> 00:32:48,925
Oh, well, it doesn't matter.
I've got her exactly where I want her.

441
00:32:49,009 --> 00:32:52,053
But I knew
what Professor Docherty would do.

442
00:32:52,137 --> 00:32:55,015
The Resistance knew about her son.

443
00:32:55,223 --> 00:32:58,393
That's why I came to find you.
Know your enemy.

444
00:32:59,561 --> 00:33:02,314
I told her about the gun
so she'd get me here.

445
00:33:02,397 --> 00:33:05,358
-At the right time.
-But you're still gonna die.

446
00:33:05,484 --> 00:33:08,612
Don't you want to know what I was doing,
travelling the world?

447
00:33:08,695 --> 00:33:11,156
-Tell me.
-I told a story. That's all.

448
00:33:11,239 --> 00:33:14,910
No weapons, just words.
I did just what the Doctor said.

449
00:33:14,993 --> 00:33:18,163
I went across the continents
all on my own.

450
00:33:18,246 --> 00:33:22,167
And everywhere I went I found the people
and I told them my story.

451
00:33:22,250 --> 00:33:26,671
He has saved your lives so many times
and you never even knew he was there.

452
00:33:26,755 --> 00:33:27,839
I know him.

453
00:33:27,923 --> 00:33:29,466
I told them about the Doctor.

454
00:33:29,591 --> 00:33:30,842
I love him.

455
00:33:30,926 --> 00:33:32,928
And I told them to pass it on.

456
00:33:33,011 --> 00:33:35,847
To spread the word so that
everyone would know about the Doctor.

457
00:33:35,931 --> 00:33:40,352
-Faith and hope? Is that all?
-No, 'cause I gave them an instruction.

458
00:33:40,894 --> 00:33:42,354
Just as the Doctor said.

459
00:33:42,437 --> 00:33:43,939
Use the countdown.

460
00:33:44,064 --> 00:33:47,734
I told them that if everyone thinks
of one word, at one specific time...

461
00:33:47,859 --> 00:33:50,737
Nothing will happen!
Is that your weapon?

462
00:33:52,030 --> 00:33:54,241
-Prayer?
-Right across the world.

463
00:33:54,366 --> 00:33:57,494
One word, just one thought,
at one moment,

464
00:33:57,577 --> 00:34:00,247
but with 15 satellites.

465
00:34:01,456 --> 00:34:03,083
-What?
-The Archangel network.

466
00:34:03,166 --> 00:34:06,169
A telepathic field
binding the whole human race together.

467
00:34:06,294 --> 00:34:08,046
With all of them,
every single person on Earth,

468
00:34:08,129 --> 00:34:09,714
thinking the same thing
at the same time.

469
00:34:09,839 --> 00:34:12,425
And that word is "Doctor".

470
00:34:21,810 --> 00:34:25,480
Stop it. No, no, no, no, you don't.

471
00:34:28,567 --> 00:34:29,734
-Doctor.
-Doctor.

472
00:34:29,818 --> 00:34:30,986
Don't...

473
00:34:31,069 --> 00:34:32,487
-ALL: Doctor!
-Doctor!

474
00:34:32,571 --> 00:34:35,824
CLIVE: Doctor.
ALL: Doctor! Doctor!

475
00:34:35,907 --> 00:34:38,159
Stop this right now! Stop it!

476
00:34:39,578 --> 00:34:41,246
-Doctor.
-Doctor.

477
00:34:41,329 --> 00:34:43,415
-Doctor.
-All: (CHANTING) Doctor!

478
00:34:43,498 --> 00:34:47,168
I've had a whole year
to tune myself into the psychic network

479
00:34:47,252 --> 00:34:49,588
and integrate with its matrices.

480
00:34:49,671 --> 00:34:51,506
I order you to stop!

481
00:34:51,590 --> 00:34:54,426
ALL: (CHANTING) Doctor!

482
00:34:57,012 --> 00:34:58,513
Doctor.

483
00:35:02,350 --> 00:35:04,519
The one thing you can't do

484
00:35:05,520 --> 00:35:07,355
is stop them thinking.

485
00:35:10,692 --> 00:35:13,570
Tell me the human race
is degenerate now,

486
00:35:14,904 --> 00:35:16,865
when they can do this.

487
00:35:24,414 --> 00:35:25,999
No!

488
00:35:26,082 --> 00:35:29,002
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

489
00:35:32,922 --> 00:35:34,758
Then I'll kill them!

490
00:35:40,555 --> 00:35:43,850
You can't do this! You can't do...
It's not fair!

491
00:35:44,934 --> 00:35:47,562
-And you know what happens now.
-No!

492
00:35:49,481 --> 00:35:50,565
No!

493
00:35:53,401 --> 00:35:55,403
No! No!

494
00:35:56,363 --> 00:35:58,365
-You wouldn't listen.
-No!

495
00:35:58,448 --> 00:36:01,534
-Because you know what I'm going to say.
-No.

496
00:36:10,877 --> 00:36:12,754
I forgive you.

497
00:36:14,714 --> 00:36:16,132
My children!

498
00:36:16,216 --> 00:36:19,552
ALL: Protect the paradox!
Protect the paradox!

499
00:36:19,636 --> 00:36:21,638
Protect the paradox!

500
00:36:22,806 --> 00:36:25,892
-Captain, the paradox machine!
-You men, with me!

501
00:36:25,975 --> 00:36:27,519
You stay here.

502
00:36:28,937 --> 00:36:30,021
No!

503
00:36:36,277 --> 00:36:38,154
Now it ends, Doctor!

504
00:36:38,738 --> 00:36:40,365
Now it ends!

505
00:36:40,657 --> 00:36:42,367
(ALARMS BLARING)

506
00:36:49,708 --> 00:36:51,710
We've all six billion spheres
heading right for us!

507
00:36:51,960 --> 00:36:54,379
We've got control of the Valiant.
You can't launch.

508
00:36:54,462 --> 00:36:59,092
Oh, but I've got this.
Black Hole Convertor inside every ship.

509
00:36:59,175 --> 00:37:03,763
If I can't have this world, Doctor,
then neither can you.

510
00:37:03,972 --> 00:37:08,143
We shall stand upon this Earth
together as it burns!

511
00:37:24,951 --> 00:37:29,080
-Can't get in, we'd get slaughtered.
-Yeah, happens to me a lot.

512
00:37:37,422 --> 00:37:39,924
Weapon after weapon after weapon.

513
00:37:40,884 --> 00:37:43,928
All you do is talk and talk and talk.

514
00:37:44,429 --> 00:37:46,514
But over all these years,

515
00:37:47,724 --> 00:37:52,353
and all these disasters, I've always had
the greatest secret of them all.

516
00:37:52,437 --> 00:37:53,855
I know you.

517
00:37:55,190 --> 00:38:00,195
Explode those ships, you kill yourself.
That's the one thing you can never do.

518
00:38:05,116 --> 00:38:06,785
Give that to me.

519
00:38:41,152 --> 00:38:45,198
Everyone, get down! Time is reversing.

520
00:39:00,755 --> 00:39:02,298
(ALL SCREAMING)

521
00:39:49,679 --> 00:39:52,056
The paradox is broken.
We've reverted back.

522
00:39:52,140 --> 00:39:55,852
One year and one day,
two minutes past eight in the morning.

523
00:39:55,935 --> 00:39:58,229
MAN ON RADIO: This is UNIT Central,
what's happened up there?

524
00:39:58,313 --> 00:40:01,232
-We just saw the President assassinated.
-See.

525
00:40:01,316 --> 00:40:04,152
Just after the President was killed,
but just before the spheres arrived.

526
00:40:04,277 --> 00:40:07,405
Everything back to normal,
planet Earth restored.

527
00:40:07,488 --> 00:40:10,658
None of it happened.
The rockets, the terror, it never was.

528
00:40:10,783 --> 00:40:13,953
-What about the spheres?
-Trapped at the end of the universe.

529
00:40:14,037 --> 00:40:16,080
But I can remember it.

530
00:40:16,164 --> 00:40:20,168
We're at the eye of the storm,
the only ones who'll ever know.

531
00:40:21,252 --> 00:40:25,006
Oh, hello! You must be Mr Jones!
We haven't actually met.

532
00:40:26,341 --> 00:40:30,303
Whoa, big fella!
You don't want to miss the party. Cuffs.

533
00:40:33,681 --> 00:40:37,602
-So, what do we do with this one?
-We kill him.

534
00:40:37,769 --> 00:40:41,356
-We execute him.
-DOCTOR: No, that's not the solution.

535
00:40:42,148 --> 00:40:45,234
Oh, I think so.

536
00:40:48,905 --> 00:40:50,949
'Cause all those things,

537
00:40:52,033 --> 00:40:53,868
they still happened.

538
00:40:54,702 --> 00:40:56,329
Because of him.

539
00:40:57,705 --> 00:41:00,249
-I saw them.
-Go on!

540
00:41:02,210 --> 00:41:03,836
Do it.

541
00:41:06,965 --> 00:41:09,425
Francine, you're better than him.

542
00:41:18,977 --> 00:41:22,063
You still haven't answered the question.
What happens to me?

543
00:41:22,146 --> 00:41:26,901
You're my responsibility from now on.
The only Time Lord left in existence.

544
00:41:27,568 --> 00:41:30,113
-Yeah, but you can't trust him.
-No.

545
00:41:30,738 --> 00:41:32,824
The only safe place for him
is the Tardis.

546
00:41:32,907 --> 00:41:36,953
You mean you're just gonna keep me?

547
00:41:37,078 --> 00:41:39,664
Mmm. If that's what I have to do.

548
00:41:42,250 --> 00:41:46,379
It's time to change.
Maybe I've been wandering for too long.

549
00:41:48,923 --> 00:41:51,217
Now I've got someone to care for.

550
00:41:51,300 --> 00:41:53,094
(GUNSHOT)

551
00:41:59,475 --> 00:42:00,935
JACK: Put it down.

552
00:42:01,019 --> 00:42:03,855
There you go.
I've got you, I've got you.

553
00:42:06,315 --> 00:42:08,985
-Always the women.
-I didn't see her.

554
00:42:11,195 --> 00:42:14,240
Dying in your arms. Happy now?

555
00:42:14,323 --> 00:42:17,285
You're not dying, don't be stupid.
It's only a bullet, just regenerate.

556
00:42:17,410 --> 00:42:19,078
-No.
-One little bullet, come on.

557
00:42:19,162 --> 00:42:21,956
I guess you don't know me so well.
I refuse.

558
00:42:22,040 --> 00:42:26,419
Regenerate, just regenerate, please.
Please, just regenerate, come on!

559
00:42:26,502 --> 00:42:30,673
And spend the rest of my life
imprisoned with you?

560
00:42:33,968 --> 00:42:37,430
But you've got to.
Come on, it can't end like this.

561
00:42:38,306 --> 00:42:41,184
You and me. All the things we've done.

562
00:42:41,309 --> 00:42:44,228
Axons! Remember the Axons,
and the Daleks.

563
00:42:46,314 --> 00:42:50,818
We're the only two left.
There's no one else.

564
00:42:53,321 --> 00:42:54,739
Regenerate!

565
00:42:56,324 --> 00:42:58,117
How about that?

566
00:43:00,870 --> 00:43:02,497
I win.

567
00:43:04,290 --> 00:43:05,666
(GROANING)

568
00:43:07,043 --> 00:43:08,294
Will it stop, Doctor?

569
00:43:11,714 --> 00:43:14,509
The drumming? Will it stop?

570
00:43:41,202 --> 00:43:43,079
(DOCTOR YELLING)

571
00:44:55,651 --> 00:44:58,070
Just to say I don't blame you.

572
00:45:01,866 --> 00:45:03,534
But who are you?

573
00:45:13,044 --> 00:45:17,215
Time was every single one
of these people knew your name.

574
00:45:18,424 --> 00:45:21,135
-Now they've all forgotten you.
-Good.

575
00:45:22,136 --> 00:45:25,139
-Back to work.
-I really don't mind, though.

576
00:45:25,306 --> 00:45:26,807
Come with me.

577
00:45:26,891 --> 00:45:29,644
Had plenty of time to think
that past year.

578
00:45:29,769 --> 00:45:31,812
The year that never was.

579
00:45:33,522 --> 00:45:36,484
And I kept thinking
about that team of mine.

580
00:45:38,069 --> 00:45:41,072
Like you said, Doctor. Responsibility.

581
00:45:41,697 --> 00:45:44,659
Defending the Earth.
Can't argue with that.

582
00:45:45,826 --> 00:45:47,286
Hey, I need that!

583
00:45:47,370 --> 00:45:50,831
I can't have you walking round
with a time-travelling teleport.

584
00:45:50,957 --> 00:45:54,919
You could go anywhere. Twice.
Second time to apologise.

585
00:45:55,378 --> 00:45:58,381
And what about me? Can you fix that?
Will I ever be able to die?

586
00:45:58,506 --> 00:46:02,635
Nothing I can do.
You're an impossible thing, Jack.

587
00:46:03,761 --> 00:46:05,763
Been called that before.

588
00:46:10,351 --> 00:46:11,519
Sir.

589
00:46:13,020 --> 00:46:14,272
Ma'am.

590
00:46:18,025 --> 00:46:20,820
But I keep wondering, what about ageing?

591
00:46:21,195 --> 00:46:23,614
'Cause I can't die,
but I keep getting older,

592
00:46:23,698 --> 00:46:26,325
the odd little grey hair, you know.

593
00:46:27,493 --> 00:46:29,370
What happens
if I live for a million years?

594
00:46:29,453 --> 00:46:31,706
I really don't know.

595
00:46:31,789 --> 00:46:34,458
Okay, vanity, sorry. Yeah.

596
00:46:35,751 --> 00:46:37,962
Can't help it. Used to be a poster boy!

597
00:46:38,045 --> 00:46:41,841
When I was a kid,
living in the Boeshane Peninsula,

598
00:46:41,924 --> 00:46:43,801
tiny little place.

599
00:46:43,884 --> 00:46:47,471
I was the first one ever
to be signed up for the Time Agency.

600
00:46:47,555 --> 00:46:51,350
They were so proud of me.
The Face of Boe they called me.

601
00:46:53,477 --> 00:46:54,979
I'll see you.

602
00:46:58,357 --> 00:46:59,734
No.

603
00:47:01,235 --> 00:47:02,611
Can't be.

604
00:47:03,154 --> 00:47:06,032
No. Definitely not. No.

605
00:47:09,952 --> 00:47:11,120
No!

606
00:47:59,960 --> 00:48:02,296
Yeah, could you put me through?

607
00:48:06,592 --> 00:48:09,637
Hi, I'm looking for
a Dr Thomas Milligan.

608
00:48:12,807 --> 00:48:14,892
Yeah? Hello?

609
00:48:16,143 --> 00:48:17,395
Hello?

610
00:48:31,617 --> 00:48:34,328
Right then! Off we go. The open road!

611
00:48:34,412 --> 00:48:38,416
There is a burst of star fire right now
over the coast of Meta Sigmafolio.

612
00:48:38,499 --> 00:48:41,794
Oh, the sky is like oil on water.

613
00:48:42,169 --> 00:48:44,880
Fancy a look? Or back in time.
We could...

614
00:48:44,964 --> 00:48:47,508
I don't know, Charles II? Henry VIII?

615
00:48:47,591 --> 00:48:50,177
I know, what about Agatha Christie!

616
00:48:50,428 --> 00:48:54,014
I'd love to meet Agatha Christie,
bet she's brilliant!

617
00:48:57,351 --> 00:48:58,853
Okay.

618
00:48:59,812 --> 00:49:01,647
-I just can't.
-Yeah.

619
00:49:03,816 --> 00:49:05,901
I've spent all these years
training to be a doctor,

620
00:49:05,985 --> 00:49:08,904
and now I've got people to look after.

621
00:49:09,029 --> 00:49:11,657
They saw half the planet slaughtered
and they're devastated.

622
00:49:11,740 --> 00:49:14,285
-I can't leave them.
-Course not.

623
00:49:24,503 --> 00:49:25,880
Thank you.

624
00:49:36,140 --> 00:49:39,310
-Martha Jones, you saved the world.
-Yes, I did.

625
00:49:40,227 --> 00:49:42,313
I spent a lot of time with you
thinking I was second best,

626
00:49:42,396 --> 00:49:44,732
but you know what?

627
00:49:44,857 --> 00:49:46,567
I am good.

628
00:49:49,653 --> 00:49:52,573
-You going to be all right?
-Always, yeah.

629
00:49:53,574 --> 00:49:54,992
Right, then.

630
00:49:55,951 --> 00:49:57,077
Bye.

631
00:50:15,095 --> 00:50:17,264
'Cause the thing is,
it's like my friend Vicky.

632
00:50:17,389 --> 00:50:19,141
She lived with this bloke,
student housing,

633
00:50:19,266 --> 00:50:22,394
there were five of them, all packed in,
and this bloke was called Shaun.

634
00:50:22,478 --> 00:50:26,315
And she loved him, she did,
she completely adored him,

635
00:50:26,440 --> 00:50:28,442
spent all day long talking about him...

636
00:50:28,526 --> 00:50:30,819
-Is this going anywhere?
-Yes.

637
00:50:31,612 --> 00:50:34,198
'Cause he never looked at her twice.

638
00:50:36,033 --> 00:50:38,577
I mean, he liked her, that was it.

639
00:50:40,955 --> 00:50:44,208
And she wasted years pining after him,
years of her life,

640
00:50:44,291 --> 00:50:46,961
'cause while he was around,
she never looked at anyone else.

641
00:50:47,044 --> 00:50:51,298
And I told her, I always said to her,
time and time again, I said,

642
00:50:51,882 --> 00:50:53,717
"Get out."”

643
00:50:59,598 --> 00:51:02,309
So this is me...getting out.

644
00:51:10,317 --> 00:51:13,487
Keep that.
'Cause I'm not having you disappear!

645
00:51:13,988 --> 00:51:18,325
If that rings, when that rings,
you'd better come running, got it?

646
00:51:18,409 --> 00:51:19,660
Got it.

647
00:51:24,540 --> 00:51:26,667
I'll see you again, mister.

648
00:52:04,163 --> 00:52:06,373
(DISTANT LAUGHTER)

649
00:52:19,136 --> 00:52:21,347
(HORN BLARING)

650
00:52:29,021 --> 00:52:30,898
What?

651
00:52:32,316 --> 00:52:33,651
What?

652
00:52:33,734 --> 00:52:35,944
(BELL RINGING)

653
00:52:41,075 --> 00:52:42,534
What?

